[[18]]

Very interested in building system and process simulations of social systems (e.g., the Michigan Department of Corrections) using beta distributions to represent the shape of failure risk (from resilience to fragility) within individual simulated people, organizations, and subsystems. For example, if the horizontal axis is the cost of failure, ranging from “low or trivial” to “high or catastrophic,” then a right-skewed distribution would represent a very fragile person or entity with a high risk of catastrophic failure (disease in a medical setting, violent behavior in a prison, dropping out in a school), while a left-skewed distribution would describe a resilient entity with a high risk of low-cost failure that yields opportunities for learning without self-destruction.
